doc.title: DreamBooth (SD-v1.5)
doc.excerpt: DreamBooth is a deep learning generation model that fine-tunes existing text-to-image models such as Stable Diffusion.
doc.body:
This is an adaptation of [DreamBooth](https://github.com/TheLastBen/fast-stable-diffusion) by [TheLastBen](https://github.com/TheLastBen) to a [RunPod Endpoint](https://www.runpod.io/endpoints). This endpoint requires the URL to a publicly accessible .zip file containing a folder of images of a concept to fine-tune the model. To dive deep into DreamBooth, look at the [original paper](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2208.12242.pdf).

## Retrieve Results & Status

**Note: For information on how to check job status and retrieve results, please refer to our [Status Endpoint Documentation](https://docs.runpod.io/reference/status).**

## Model Upload (s3Config)

The DreamBooth endpoint can be used to return custom images, return a trained model, or both. To receive back the trained model, you must provide your credentials to an S3-compatible bucket.

params.desc: If True, provide the previous output of the model as a prompt for the next window; disabling may make the text inconsistent across windows, but the model becomes less prone to getting stuck in a failure loop.

params.name: input.temperature_increment_on_fallback
params.desc: Temperature to increase when falling back when the decoding fails to meet either of the thresholds below.

params.name: input.compression_ratio_threshold
params.desc: If the gzip compression ration is higher than this value, treat the decoding as failed.

params.name: input.logprob_threshold
params.desc: If the average log probability is lower than this value, treat the decoding as failed.

params.name: input.no_speech_threshold
params.desc: If the probability of the <|nospeech|> token is higher than this value AND the decoding has failed due to 'logprob_threshold', consider the segment as silence.

params.name: input
params.desc: Inputs to be generated.

params.name: input.prompt
params.default: Who is the president of the United States?

params.name: run_type
params.desc: Decides whether to run this asynchronously or synchronously. If you use "run", then it will be run async and you must use the "Receive Output/Status" endpoint with the run id to get your result.

params.name: input.sampling_params.max_tokens
params.desc: Maximum number of tokens to generate per output sequence.

params.name: input.sampling_params.n
params.desc: Number of output sequences to return for the given prompt.

params.name: input.sampling_params.best_of
params.desc: Number of output sequences that are generated from the prompt. From these `best_of` sequences, the top `n` sequences are returned. `best_of` must be greater than or equal to `n`. This is treated as the beam width when `use_beam_search` is True. By default, `best_of` is set to `n`.

params.name: input.sampling_params.presence_penalty
params.desc: Float that penalizes new tokens based on whether they appear in the generated text so far. Values > 0 encourage the model to use new tokens, while values < 0 encourage the model to repeat tokens.

params.name: input.sampling_params.frequency_penalty
params.desc: Float that penalizes new tokens based on their frequency in the generated text so far. Values > 0 encourage the model to use new tokens, while values < 0 encourage the model to repeat tokens.

params.name: input.sampling_params.temperature
params.desc: Float that controls the randomness of the sampling. Lower values make the model more deterministic, while higher values make the model more random. Zero means greedy sampling.

params.name: input.sampling_params.top_p
params.desc: Float that controls the cumulative probability of the top tokens to consider. Must be in (0, 1]. Set to 1 to consider all tokens.

params.name: input.sampling_params.top_k
params.desc: Integer that controls the number of top tokens to consider. Set to -1 to consider all tokens.

params.name: input.sampling_params.use_beam_search
params.desc: Whether to use beam search instead of sampling.

params.name: input.sampling_params.stop
params.desc: List of strings that stop the generation when they are generated. The returned output will not contain the stop strings.

params.name: input.sampling_params.ignore_eos
params.desc: Whether to ignore the EOS token and continue generating tokens after the EOS token is generated.

params.name: input.sampling_params.logprobs
params.desc: Number of log probabilities to return per output token.
